16
00:01:35,740 --> 00:01:42,100
The schwa goes with the syllabic consonants L, M, N, and R.
中元音与音节辅音 L、M、N 和 R 搭配。

17
00:01:43,220 --> 00:01:50,480
That means when you have a syllable with a schwa, followed by one of these consonants, you don't need to make the schwa.
这意味着当你有一个中元音音节，后面跟着这些辅音之一时，你不需要发出中元音。

18
00:01:50,660 --> 00:01:53,400
It gets absorbed by the next sound.
